  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Why are so many Quora users posting questions that are readily answered on Google?",
  "response": "There are several reasons why users might post questions on Quora that could easily be answered with a quick Google search:\n\n1. **Desire for Personalized Responses**: Quora allows users to receive answers from real people, often experts or enthusiasts in the field, who can provide personalized, detailed, or nuanced responses. This can be more valuable than a generic search result.\n\n2. **Human Interaction**: Some users prefer the social aspect of asking questions and engaging in discussions with others. They may seek community input, different perspectives, or even just the reassurance of human interaction.\n\n3. **Question Clarity and Specificity**: Users might have very specific or complex questions that they feel are better addressed by knowledgeable individuals rather than by sifting through multiple search results.\n\n4. **Trust in Community Knowledge**: Quora has built a reputation as a platform where experts and knowledgeable users contribute. People may trust the answers from this community more than anonymous search results.\n\n5. **Ease of Use**: For some, it\u2019s easier to type out a question on Quora and wait for responses rather than navigating through multiple websites and sources.\n\n6. **Search Skill Variability**: Not everyone is skilled at using search engines effectively. Some users might find it challenging to frame their queries in a way that yields useful results from Google.\n\n7. **Desire for Current Information**: Quora can provide up-to-date information and insights, whereas some Google results might be outdated or static.\n\n8. **Laziness or Habit**: Sometimes, users might simply be lazy or habitual in their behavior, opting for the convenience of asking on a familiar platform rather than conducting their own research.\n\n9. **Social Proof and Validation**: By asking on Quora, users can see how many people agree with a particular answer, which can provide a sense of validation or social proof.\n\n10. **SEO and Visibility**: Some users might be trying to increase their visibility on Quora by asking frequently searched or popular questions, thereby boosting their profile or engagement metrics.\n\nEach user\u2019s motivation might vary, but these are some of the common reasons why people turn to Quora even for questions that could be answered via a Google search.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
